			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ya cant beat it. With the buff spell that comes with this at lvl 44 you can easily destroy many mobs. Here is what I do usually. I go into EW and look for a high lvl rhino or if I`m lucky a griffon is up. Always Always Always snare first. Then move out of range and as the target returns into your range cast uopn it. Now the easy part, find a target( I prefer giants for faction) and send pet on it. Snare the giant then buff pet. Now nuke it hard 1 time and get aggro. Move away from the giant then sit down. As he approaches you (pet wailing on him the whole time) get up and move a little farther away. Do this till pet regains aggro then nuke hard again. By now he`ll be dead. That burned 1.5m-2m at lvl 50 with 183 wis after the fight is done. Remeber that ya medding while letting it aggro to you. I like to charm  the rhinos for their hps or the griffons for their high damage. You can repeat this many times. If the pet survives and you run oom this is a key to your survival and not having to zone or gate. Keep fear memmed and always target your pet after a fight. You can control your pet as well so just make him sit away from you while you med. Charm breaks resnare then fear or recharm if mana allows. Piece of cake. Some other things to note: pet can be healed (but not DS`d..go figure) and the pet will draw aggro just as if it were you. So if ya run off too far from him he may have a surprise waiting for ya when ya run back.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
