			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Got a few charming techniques for any open-minded druids who'd like to try them. Charming is the only way i solo now, and it's very safe and mana-efficient.  Always begin by snaring your pet, making it quite harmless even if charm wears off.  Then find another animal and snare it as well.  use a spell from the Fear Animal line on it, and have your pet attack it. This way, your pet takes no damage while you sit nearby and med. When you finally begin to run low on mana, have your pet attack something but *don't* fear it. this way, the pet takes damage. buff/heal as needed so your pet wins, but not by much. Then camo yourself (making your pet hate you) and kite it. i usually end up with 5 or 6 blue conning kills on one bar of mana. definately worth a try.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
