	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				\\This spell shoud be like all the other per spells, permanent unlesss you zone. \<BR>
I'm assuming you meant like all other pet spells.  Unfortunately this and the Enchanter charm spell, aren't like all other pet spells.  This doesn't summon anything, but charms a nearby animal.  If this lasted until you zone, it would be way too much power for a character to have.  You could set your group on the toughest mob and cast charm until it stuck and have one of the best pets in the zone.  There has to be some danger in charming something that's roaming around, and that is for the charm to fail or wear off, causing the target to aggo.  Other classes pet spells, create a pet out of inanimate (sp?) material, if the spell fails there's no aggro'd mob to worry about.  Also, these pets die when the owner zones, unlike charmed pets that I believe become normal mobs with normal mob characteristics (unless buffed by the charmer).<BR>
<BR>
Straith 36 druid  Bristlebane.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
